EXCLUDABILITY SWEEP (mean-field). cell P=1.0 L=5, kappa=2, cost=1.
r = private fraction of confiscated payoff. Same suppression & extraction throughout.

    r   alpha*    <fE>    <fD>     <R>   regime
  0.0     2.60   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.1     2.60   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.2     2.70   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.3     2.60   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.4     2.50   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.5     2.40   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.6     2.30   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.7     2.20   0.008   0.002     0.0   collapse (enforcers dead)
  0.8     0.50   0.389   0.151    72.3   coexistence
  0.9     0.50   0.458   0.118    80.2   stable protection
  1.0     0.50   0.479   0.107    84.6   stable protection

Look for: collapse -> coexistence -> stable protection as r rises, and the r* where
enforcers first persist (fE lifts off the floor). That r* is the excludability threshold.
